<p><span class="fw">1806</span>
</p>
<p>July</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">exposed with their clothes under their arms through crowds of spectators to their own huts where they often continue chatting to the first that comes to hand before they dress or got to bed.  The men in the summer make use of no covering than their robes and then only when they are out visiting.  At night they sleep naked like so many brutes.  This Evening we were teazed for some time with young women offering their Services which being declined they retired much dissatisfied.  About midnight we were disturbed in our sleep.  I went to the door and perceived a considerable crowd of naked <span class="AddHand-author">people </span>going about singing and dancing.  The meaning of this frolic which lasted two hours we could not learn<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  However nothing could be more inde<span class="AddHand-author">s</span>ent than their appearance<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Young men I observed keep watch during night either sitting on the tops of the huts or walking round the Village Singing songs.  Their manner of making love is not as among other nations by Entering the tent and laying down quietly by their Mistresses.  Their custom is to sing love songs out of doors near enough to be heard and understood by their beloved who either comes <span class="DelHand-author">and</span> <span class="AddHand-author">out</span> and joins immediately or remains until day when they repair to the corn fields</p>
<p style="text-align:right;">followed</p>

